org.ndnx.ndn.profiles.versioning
Class VersionNumber

java.lang.Object
  org.ndnx.ndn.profiles.versioning.VersionNumber
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<VersionNumber>, ContentName.ComponentProvider
public class VersionNumber
extends Object
implements Comparable<VersionNumber>, ContentName.ComponentProvider

Represent the version used in a NDNx name. The core of this is based on a NDNTime, but NDNTime has two different uses (getTime as long since epoch and binaryTime), which ends up being confusing. This class should eventually be updated to just operate on the raw byte array. A version number is an immutable object. This class is currently only used in the versioning package, not in the VersioningProfile or elsewhere in the code.

getComponent

public byte[] getComponent()
Specified by:
getComponent in interface ContentName.ComponentProvider
Returns:
Fetches a component. The byte array that is returned must be immutable - i.e. never get changed. If there is any risk the byte array you have may be changed you must return a new copy of it.
